properties.Name: ShipmentRouteLeg
properties.Description:
The route leg that a shipment transits (already has transited) or is planned to transit.

Note that a shipment route can be changed or modified and then the leg may have a status of:

- Leg Planned
- Leg Scheduled
- Leg Modified From Original Planned Leg
- Leg Completed

Columns.Name: ShipmentId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Shipment.

Columns.Name: ShipmentLegNumber
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Shipment Leg Number, which equals the shipment leg 'sequence number'.

Columns.Name: ShipmentMethodId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Shipment Method.

Columns.Name: ShipmentRouteNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the shipment route/leg.

Columns.Name: CarrierId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Carrier.

Columns.Name: CarrierRouteId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Carrier Route.

Columns.Name: CarrierRouteLegNumber
Columns.Description: The assigned to the Carrier Route Leg.

Columns.Name: RouteLegTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Route Leg Type.

Columns.Name: ExpectedCarrierChargeAmount
Columns.Description: The amount expected to be charged by the carrier based on the carrier route schedule.

Columns.Name: ShipmentLegFromLocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the From-Location.

Columns.Name: ShipmentLegToLocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the To-Location.

Columns.Name: PlannedEarliestPickUpTimestamp
Columns.Description: The earliest that the shipment items can be picked up.

Columns.Name: PlannedLatestPickUpTimestamp
Columns.Description: The latest that the shipment items can be picked-up.

Columns.Name: PlannedEarliestDeliveryTimestamp
Columns.Description: The earliest that the shipment items can be delivered.

Columns.Name: PlannedLatestDeliveryTimestamp
Columns.Description: The latest that the shipment items can be delivered.

Columns.Name: PlannedDepartureTimestamp
Columns.Description: The planned departure timestamp.

Columns.Name: PlannedArrivalTimestamp
Columns.Description: The planned arrival timestamp.

Columns.Name: ActualDepartureTimestamp
Columns.Description: The actual departure timestamp.

Columns.Name: ActualArrivalTimestamp
Columns.Description: The actual arrival timestamp.

Columns.Name: AssetReplacementOccurredIndicator
Columns.Description:
Indicates that the replacement of an Asset occurred during the shipment leg.  

Ex:
- Truck had to be replaced

Columns.Name: BackhaulLegIndicator
Columns.Description: To haul a shipment back over part of a route it has traveled.

Columns.Name: InterlineCargoTransferLocationIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the cargo is arriving at a point by one carrier and continuing its journey through another carrier.

Columns.Name: PlannedCarrierId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Carrier.

Columns.Name: PlannedFlightNumber
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Flight.

Columns.Name: PlannedFlightDate
Columns.Description: The date of the Flight.

Columns.Name: PlannedFlightLegDepartureAirportCode
Columns.Description:
AKA Airport Code

Three-letter codes used to identify airports.

Airport Code 
The airport code is a three letter designator for a commercial airport, or other travel point -- e.g. a large bus station. These are the codes that airlines and pilots use to identify airports and are used in timetables, baggage tags, tickets, advertisements, Airline and Global Reservation Systems. There are approximately 9,000 of them in use of a total of 17,576 available
